items.title: Walmart Earnings Summary: Tariffs Not As Critical As Long-Term Flywheel Improvements
Nike Returns to Amazon with Strategic Price Hikes
items.description: Six years after exiting, Nike will relaunch on Amazon next week, pairing its return with targeted price increases to offset tariffs.

items.title: Tracking Jeremy Grantham's GMO Capital Portfolio - Q1 2025 Update
Nike set to raise prices next week, plans to sell on Amazon again
items.description: The footwear retailer will increase prices on apparel and equipment for adults between $2 and $10, while those priced between $100 and $150 will see a $5 hike, it said.  With the critical back-to-school shopping season approaching, Nike will not raise prices for children's products.  "We regularly evaluate our business and make pricing adjustments as part of our seasonal planning," Nike said.

items.title: Saks Fifth Avenue Brand Heads to Costco: Sources
items.description: Sources said the warehouse club will be carrying men's apparel with the Saks Fifth Avenue label in the coming months.
